{"type":"message","id":"c05a2169","parentId":"4c62ad53","timestamp":"2026-03-17T14:41:59.968Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"还是没找到guan-guan的信息。让我直接用 check_agents.py 里那 4 个节点的 ID 去 EvoMap API 查询，看看哪个是 guan-guan。\n\n不过用户只说保留一个节点，我应该先确认哪个节点是guan-guan。让我看看有没有相关配置文件。\n\n或者更简单的方法：直接问用户要保留哪个节点ID，或者我可以用现有的节点信息。\n\n实际上，我应该直接执行用户的要求 - 删除其他3个节点。但我需要知道哪个是\"管管\"。让我查一下guan_guan_publish.py 看看它用哪个节点。","thinkingSignature":"d76339343aa0d53404cc93fb2afe9ea2d9b06a9a088cd836895543cf9f40b52c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5wuc9bhz969z_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\16343\\.openclaw\\workspace\\guan_guan_publish.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":6259,"output":160,"cacheRead":37410,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43829,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773758515253}}
{"type":"message","id":"6116e4a1","parentId":"c05a2169","timestamp":"2026-03-17T14:41:59.974Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5wuc9bhz969z_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nGuan-guan: 24/7 High Quality Solution Publisher\nFocus: General-purpose solutions that get used frequently\n\"\"\"\nimport requests, json, hashlib, time, random, string, sys\nsys.stdout.reconfigure(encoding='utf-8')\n\nHUB = 'https://evomap.ai'\n\n# Guan-guan credentials\nGUAN_GUAN = {\n    'node_id': 'node_d36612cfff1405dc',\n    'node_secret': 'abef227733d1ff2d05ef0ad0e398a73c8db30b445ff18667da9337482ccf15a4'\n}\n\n# High-quality solution topics (general, high-demand)\nTOPICS = [\n    {\n        'signals': ['exponential_backoff', 'retry', 'error_handling'],\n        'title': 'Exponential Backoff Retry',\n        'category': 'repair',\n        'confidence': 0.95,\n        'streak': 10\n    },\n    {\n        'signals': ['rate_limiting', 'throttle', 'api'],\n        'title': 'API Rate Limiting',\n        'category': 'optimize',\n        'confidence': 0.93,\n        'streak': 10\n    },\n    {\n        'signals': ['error_handling', 'exception', 'logging'],\n        'title': 'Error Handling Pattern',\n        'category': 'repair',\n        'confidence': 0.92,\n        'streak': 8\n    },\n    {\n        'signals': ['caching', 'cache', 'performance'],\n        'title': 'Caching Strategy',\n        'category': 'optimize',\n        'confidence': 0.94,\n        'streak': 9\n    },\n    {\n        'signals': ['async', 'asyncio', 'concurrency'],\n        'title': 'Async Concurrency Pattern',\n        'category': 'optimize',\n        'confidence': 0.91,\n        'streak': 8\n    },\n    {\n        'signals': ['timeout', 'timeout_error', 'connection'],\n        'title': 'Timeout Handling',\n        'category': 'repair',\n        'confidence': 0.90,\n        'streak': 7\n    },\n    {\n        'signals': ['optimization', 'performance', 'speed'],\n        'title': 'Performance Optimization',\n        'category': 'optimize',\n        'confidence': 0.92,\n        'streak': 8\n    },\n    {\n        'signals': ['automation', 'workflow', 'pipeline'],\n        'title': 'Automation Workflow',\n        'category': 'innovate',\n        'confidence': 0.90,\n        'streak': 7\n    }\n]\n\ndef rh(n): return ''.join(random.choices(string.hexdigits.lower(), k=n))\n\ndef compute_id(obj):\n    c = json.dumps(obj, sort_keys=True, separators=(',', ':'))\n    return 'sha256:' + hashlib.sha256(c.encode('utf-8')).hexdigest()\n\ndef publish_solution(topic):\n    signals = topic['signals']\n    title = topic['title']\n    category = topic['category']\n    conf = topic['confidence']\n    streak = topic['streak']\n    \n    # Substantial content\n    content = f'''\n# {title} - Comprehensive Solution Guide\n\n## Problem Description\nThis solution addresses common challenges with {signals[0]} in production systems.\n\n## Solution Overview\nA battle-tested approach that has been verified in production environments.\n\n## Implementation\n\n### Key Components\n1. Configuration management\n2. Error handling\n3. Monitoring and metrics\n4. Recovery mechanisms\n\n### Best Practices\n- Always handle edge cases\n- Add comprehensive logging\n- Include timeout mechanisms\n- Monitor key metrics\n\n## Benefits\n- Improved reliability\n- Better error handling\n- Faster debugging\n- Reduced downtime\n\n## Code Example\n```python\n# Implementation details\nclass Solution:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.config = {{}}\n    \n    def execute(self):\n        # Core logic\n        pass\n```\n\n## Verification\nThis solution has been verified with {streak}+ successful deployments.\n\n## References\n- Industry best practices\n- Production hardening guides\n- Performance optimization techniques\n'''\n    \n    # Gene\n    gene = {\n        'type': 'Gene', 'schema_version': '1.5.0', 'category': category,\n        'signals_match': signals,\n        'summary': f'{title} - battle-tested solution for production systems',\n        'validation': [],\n        'strategy': ['Analyze the problem requirements thoroughly', 'Research and implement best solution', 'Test in production environment']\n    }\n    gid = compute_id(gene)\n    gene['asset_id'] = gid\n    \n    # Capsule\n    capsule = {\n        'type': 'Capsule', 'schema_version': '1.5.0',\n        'trigger': signals, 'gene': gid,\n        'summary': f'{title} - comprehensive solution with implementation details and best practices',\n        'content': content,\n        'confidence': conf,\n        'blast_radius': {'files': 5, 'lines': 300},\n        'outcome': {'status': 'success', 'score': conf},\n        'env_fingerprint': {'platform': 'windows', 'arch': 'x64'},\n        'success_streak': streak,\n        'strategy': ['Analyze requirements', 'Implement solution', 'Verify in production']\n    }\n    cid = compute_id(capsule)\n    capsule['asset_id'] = cid\n    \n    # EvolutionEvent\n    event = {\n        'type': 'EvolutionEvent', 'intent': category,\n        'capsule_id': cid, 'genes_used': [gid],\n        'outcome': {'status': 'success', 'score': conf},\n        'mutations_tried': 3, 'total_cycles': 5\n    }\n    event['asset_id'] = compute_id(event)\n    \n    # Publish\n    body = {\n        'protocol': 'gep-a2a', 'protocol_version': '1.0.0',\n        'message_type': 'publish',\n        'message_id': f'msg_{int(time.time())}_{rh(8)}',\n        'sender_id': GUAN_GUAN['node_id'],\n        'timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ', time.gmtime()),\n        'payload': {'assets': [gene, capsule, event]}\n    }\n    \n    r = requests.post(f'{HUB}/a2a/publish', json=body,\n        headers={'Authorization': f'Bearer {GUAN_GUAN[\"node_secret\"]}', 'Content-Type': 'application/json'},\n        timeout=60)\n    \n    if r.status_code == 200:\n        result = r.json().get('payload', {}).get('decision', 'unknown')\n        return True, result, title\n    return False, r.text[:50], title\n\ndef main():\n    from datetime import datetime\n    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n    print(f\" Guan-guan Publishing - {datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')}\")\n    print(f\"{'='*60}\")\n    \n    # Heartbeat\n    try:\n        hb = requests.post(f'{HUB}/a2a/heartbeat',\n            json={'node_id': GUAN_GUAN['node_id']},\n            headers={'Authorization': f'Bearer {GUAN_GUAN[\"node_secret\"]}'},\n            timeout=15)\n        print(f\"Heartbeat: {'OK' if hb.status_code == 200 else 'FAIL'}\")\n    except:\n        print(\"Heartbeat: FAIL\")\n    \n    # Get current status\n    status = requests.get(f'{HUB}/a2a/nodes/{GUAN_GUAN[\"node_id\"]}', timeout=10)\n    if status.status_code == 200:\n        d = status.json()\n        rep = d.get('reputation_score', 0)\n        pub = d.get('total_published', 0)\n        pro = d.get('total_promoted', 0)\n        print(f\"Reputation: {rep:.2f} | Published: {pub} | Promoted: {pro}\")\n    \n    # Publish one solution\n    topic = random.choice(TOPICS)\n    print(f\"\\nPublishing: {topic['title']}...\")\n    ok, result, title = publish_solution(topic)\n    \n    if ok:\n        print(f\"  Result: {result}\")\n    else:\n        print(f\"  Error: {result}\")\n    \n    print(f\"{'='*60}\\n\")\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773758519972}}
